Remove batching to the main thread. Texture uploads to the GPU are a fixed cost and by batching we actually group that cost which might actually cause missed frame deadlines. Multiple posts in the same frame isn't really an issue either as layout is already batched. Also this was speculatively added without empirical data to justify its presence.

Merge pull request #1817 from square/jrod/versions Add versions plugin
Add versions plugin Also, bump Truth

Replace MarkableInputStream with a superior Okio version. This new InputStream uses the Buffer of the supplied BufferedSource to ensure it has buffered the necessary bytes to fulfill the reads of the consumer (via copies). This allows the original source to still be consumed normally by virtue of the fact that we never read directly from it.

There's a host of tests that we need for this but I'm holding off on writing them because we might actually upstream a mechanism similar to this into Okio.

Merge pull request #1563 from dlew/dlew/fix-offline-retries Retry requests even when there is no connectivity

Retry requests even when there is no connectivity BitmapHunter was intended to eventually retry using NetworkPolicy.OFFLINE
if there were enough failed retries. However, the code was (at
some point) changed so that it would not retry if you had no connectivity.
These two behaviors were at odds, so I changed it back to depending

Merge pull request #855 from dlew/dlew/transition-drawable Use TransitionDrawable for PicassoDrawable

Fixing Message memory leaks Prior to Android L, the VM caches stack local variables in blocking loops. This can lead to memory leaks of messages for threads that become inactive but aren't shutdown. This change ensure that we never leak for too long and always replace the leaking reference.

These memory leaks tend to be problematic when using Picasso in an app that also uses Dialogs, because Dialogs obtain template Message instance that are never recycled. These messages are listeners and often hold references to the activity. When the dialog is GCed, the messages should be GCed too but they aren't because of the thread stack local message leak.
